# Gitignore Maintenance

- Whenever adding new tools, frameworks, or testing libraries (like Playwright, Jest, etc.), you MUST evaluate if the `.gitignore` needs to be updated.
- Ensure build artifacts, test results, coverage reports, caches, and environment variable files are ignored.
- Common directories to ignore when adding testing/build tools:
  - `test-results/`
  - `playwright-report/`
  - `coverage/`
  - `dist/` or `build/`
  - `.cache/`
- Do not commit `.env` or `.local` files containing secrets or local configuration.
- When adding scratch/debug workflows, ensure root-level artifacts (screenshots, `.tmp`, `.bak`, `scratch/`, `debug/`) stay ignored — see the repo-hygiene rule.
